He sit in her chair, while he looked at her with mist in his eyes.
"I feel like a failure" his shoulder shaking, "like I'm not doing as much as I could... or want to"
"I understand" she said.
"Like there are things in my life I want, but I'm not achieving" he continued as if she's not speaking at all, "like I watched myself falling apart, but I'm doing nothing about it"
She let him pouring every grief, every untold story into his unshed tears.
.
You're allowed to grieve. Grief is not only occur when someone passed away. You grieve when your relationship broken. You grieve when your dream shattered. You grieve when your opportunity crushed.
.
"I know you feel like a failure" looking directly in his eyes, she continued, "but you're going to be okay"
.
.
.
.
.

caption.text:
I have been an avid follower of kak Atikah @thetudungtraveller, she is a Singaporean social activist. Her posts always inspires me to be a better Muslim Woman. Also I know there is a social project of her: #rainbowforbatam, which is a fundraising and volunteering for children homes in Batam. But I never really know much about the project before, and since I live in Jakarta now, there seemed no point in pursuing for more information. Yet a few months ago I decided to ask her about how to getting more involved. Luckily they had an event for Hari Raya Celebration with the kids which was when I still on my holiday breaks in Batam.
.
Long story shorts, Kak Atikah let me joined #rainbowforbatam, even though this time the gathering supposed for alumni and member only, and all of them are Singaporeans. I feel honored to be with amazing people like them. And spending time with the kids feels like some part of me heals; I didn't even know that I am bruised and broken before. I had a blast of time and I cerished each moments very much.
.
One thing I realize during working with them is:
It doesn't matter what age you are now, whether you are man or woman, whether you grow up with different culture or not, whether you have a privilege of sophistication or still struggling with modernization or whatever your nationality is, Indonesian or Singaporean or any citizenship in this world. Ultimately what makes you get along working together is when you have the same passions and pursuing the same goals. And in here, their passions towards helping others in need, giving back and sharing whatever they have generously is what bonding them together. And this matters.
.
I am very amazed with each one of them, the way they interact with the kids and what this trip means to them, even as the chaos of shopping spree for the kids we did, made a memorable moment that I found myself smiling every time i thought about it.
.
Thank you for inviting me to be part of #rainbowforbatam. I can't wait for more trips you make by the ferry, crossing the oceanüòäüòäüòä
.
.
.
.
~~~You don't really lose something when you giving back, because essentially you will find a little bit of yourself along the way ~~

caption.text:
‚óè Concordance ‚óè
.
.
Have you ever been content just to watch from the perimeter of what‚Äôs going on in your surrounding?
Have you ever been so at ease with a place to fit in perfectly?
Have you ever stood right at the brink of where the tumult and crashing was just out of reach because you understood the boundaries?
Have you ever just let it go because you have seen zenith and nadir of life? 
Have you ever been so in tune with your environment that you can relax in a heightened state of readiness?
.
I haven‚Äôt.
.
But sometimes I
Glimpse the harmony,
Clutch a shred of solidity,
Catch a snippet of balance,
And witness the concord for myself.
.
And so I go back,
To find it,
To find home,
To find my place.
.
.
.
.

caption.text:
Beauty and the Beast : Part Two.
(Refers to previous post for part one)
.
Wait. Rolled back that for a minute üòïüòï
How do I know if I chose to stay in an abusive relationship, my Beast will truly change into Prince Charming?
How long do I have to stay?
How many violence I've to endure?
What if it takes ages?
What if it's never come to an end?
For God sake, this time it would be a reality, not another happily-ever-after Disney movie.
.
And that's where the domestic violence usually start; when the woman thinks she could change the beast inside a man.
Statistics suggests one of six women have endured domestic violence, and this number is likely to be higher.
It was getting worse when there's child involve.
Could you imagine what would happen to an innocent child exposed or even received these domestic violence?
.
Well, at the end Disney movie is all about happily ever after.
If it wasn't for my extensive research, I won't even thought about this dark tragedy, and all the what-ifs involved.
I did enjoy watching the movie and surprisingly I also enjoy the play.
.
Notes for my Beast out there: go change yourself first, don't wait for me to change you. Meanwhile, I will do the same change, to be a better version of myself. Therefore, by the time we meet, we will be a Beauty and the Prince Charming for each other. üëçüëç
.
Ps: if life as a statisticians got to dull, should I try actress for change? üòÇüòÇüòÇ
.
#BeautyandtheBeast #DomesticViolence #AbusiveRelationship #FoodForThought #DisneyMovie

Beauty and the Beast : Part One.
.
In spirit of the dress I wear, I want to address a few things that have been niggling my conscience. Beware this will be a very long food-for-thought post. üòÖüòÖ
.
This wasn't a first time I watched Beauty and the Beast. I had watched the animation version since I was a little girl. But, in order to fully grasp how to act like Belle, I brought myself to rewatch it again and did some extensive research about her.
And guess what I have found??
Too much dark tragedy involved between the lines in the movie.
.
Even though the play that I was part of, way too different from the original story plot - even Belle in this play was a Queen now - I can't help myself to forget what I've found: Abusive Relationship.
.
Abusive relationship takes any form: physical, verbal, social, financial, and emotional. And in this movie, Belle was definitely in an abusive relationship, at least in the beginning. Beast might never condone any physical violence toward Belle - not directly at least - but he puts a lot of verbal assault toward her.
.
The thing that niggling me the most was: when Belle chose to stay even though she had an opportunity to leave the beast for good; although that's what brought changed to the Beast at the end.
If I were Belle, I know I won't stay.
If I had an opportunity to leave an abusive relationship, I would grab it with both hands and run as fast as I could.
.
Then, where it would leave the Beast?
He would continue to be the beast, to condone any violence he seemed fit to get what he wanted.
No chance for him to be the Prince Charming.
.

She was name hope, after her parents hope fulfilled for an adorable baby girl
"Hope" he said to her.
"Yes" she answered.
"Do you know what hope means?" He asked her.
He was known as a wanderer, so instead of answered his question, she indulgent him, "Why don't you tell me?"
"According to the old version of English dictionary, hope was a combination of desire and confidence"
She still; she couldn't say anything. She knew what was coming when he continued "And right now, what I desired the most was not what I was confident about" he finished sheepishly.
It was silent after that. Neither one of them try to break the spell. She understood completely what he was saying. It was there in the air. Her name. Hope. And what it means to him.

caption.text:
Two days ago I was listening to the news coverage of Manchester bombing during Ariana Grande concert. It was devastating. I imagine the victims will be young energetic people in my group age. Concert supposed to be a safe place; it was no more.
.
Last night, at nine when the night still young, another tragedy happened. Suicidal bomb in a bus station. In another public place, where people gather to get a means of transportation.
.
This time, it was close to home, figuratively and literally speaking.
The bus station is only fifteen minutes walking distances from where I live.
It was as close as Harbor Springs High School to bookstore in downtown Harbor.
It was as close as Times Square to Central Park where you jogging every evening.
It was as close as Merlion Park to Marina Sand Bay where you could see the building clearly.
Twenty meters from the bus station was a bakery where I usually get cakes for celebration, even my birthday cake bought in there.
If you walk to the next two store, there's a pizza place where my friends and I hang out when we craved for pizza.
.
There were traffics. Ambulances sirens kept ringing all night. The place still roaming with many people, media, authorities. The crowd buzz stills talked about the tragedy the whole time since it happened.
.
I am scared.
I feel fear.
I am anxious to get out.
.
Some of my friends try to have a normal day as usual. And I did try to do so. But here I am, still contemplating my fears. My mind keeps playing it tricks; put me where my anxiety and worry is.
.
They told me don't be afraid.
They told me Jakarta is safe.
They told me we should stay strong.
.
Fear only gives the terrorist more ammunition. It's a benchmark to measure their success in this tragedy. My fears is what the terrorist want to see and they sure will love it. They thirst for it.
.
But I am still scared. I am okay physically, but the terror keeps ringing in my mind.
.
I pray for the victims.
I pray for the innocent lives.
I pray for the fears in people heart and minds.
I pray...
.
#JakartaBombing #JakartaSafe #WeAreNotAfraid #ManchesterBombing #ManchesterSafe #PrayforJakarta #PrayforManchester #ItsOkay #IWillbeOkay #PrayfortheInnocent

Bismillahir rahmanir rahim.
In the name of Allah, the Most Gracious, the Most Merciful 
If I have learned anything this year, it is that I know what I want and I am aware of what I deserve. I have learned to stop saying yes when I don't mean it - to live as authentically as I know. I find comfort in knowing that whatever I lose most likely never deserved to be kept by me.

We shouldn't discriminate humans based on looks, blemishes, scars, and disfigurement.

I am looking forward now to where sky meets sea. All the infinite possibility. And as one door opens and another closes, I will move forward with the knowledge that unlike so many others, I have another year ahead of me - another shot at making it all the way around the sun, and the chance to get it right this time.

To read more, to write more, to travel more, to struggle more, and to smile more on this journey Home to Jannah. Insya Allah. God Willing!

Finally I have decided to do what my mom insisted me to: pay a doctor a visit. For me it's nothing serious, only a sore throat (so my voice sounds like a frog) and a headache. I was thinking probably because of the weather.
So I mentioned to the doctor of my sore throat and headache, try to keep it brief, because I am not really a big fan of medical institutions. And the doctor surprised me by saying that I am depressed. I have to let my brain relax, do not think too much. Stress out about a lot of stuff is not good for the rest of my body.

On my way back, i keep playing the conversation. Did I just visit a doctor or psychiatric??
Anyway, I try to take the advice, let go the issues that bite my brain. Stop beating myself for the mistakes I have done in the past. Stop worrying about the future. Not a single anxiety will change what happen later.
And I decide to cut some slacks on my life. I learn to say NO to some engagements. I am not indispensable, others probably could do better without me. I am stop labeling myself irresponsible, careless, or coward, for not showing up or for make mistakes.

I take a deep breath and try to relax my brain. At the end, the world will be still living without my intervention there. At the end, I am just me. So it's okay for not be the part of anything.

They will be alright.
It will be alright.
I will be alright.

This keeps the man from falling into the dragon's jaws, or being eaten by the monster above, but it turns out there's another little problem. Two mice, one black and one white, are scurrying around and around the branch, nibbling it. It's only a matter of time before they will chew through the branch, causing the man to fall. As the man contemplates his inescapable fate, he notices something else: from the end of the branch he's holding, a few drops of honey are dripping. The man sticks out his tongue to lick them. This [...] is our human predicament: we're the man clutching the branch. Death awaits us. There is no escape. And so we distract ourselves by licking whatever drops of honey come within our reach.
Eugenides

Another new year resolution :)
Well, I have read this passage a few days ago, and it's really hit me right in the heart... '.....You have the feeling that you don't belong, when you are in the job interview and your hair is "too natural".
You have the feeling of embarrassment, when you are in the shop and the security guard starts following you.
Your words and opinions, your beliefs and convictions isn't important because you aren't the right type of human being for this particular society.
You have that feeling of shame when you get to the party and you are the only "one" there, nobody says it but they let you know with their eyes and their actions.
You have that undermining feeling, when you are trying really hard, but certain businesses won't work with you, because you are the "right look", but you are "too political" even though everything they do is political.
You don't belong, they make you feel this way everyday.. but **** them, who are they?
Just another human beings with closed minds, limited views, and disgusting attitudes. You find your own path and you walk it.....' Well.. I want to change, I want to create a new world, where I belong, where I fit in. So this new year resolution is all about change... the change in me... You will find me seeking knowledge, as this is how we grow. I have a lot to learn and the more I study, I learn there is much to know.
You will find me avoiding vanity because I won't destroy my soul, I keep away from materialism because my love cannot be bought or sold.
You will find me lost in the right direction, immersed in our amazing universe, searching for nothing and finding everything.
You will find me connecting with beautiful souls, on a spritual, emotional, and intellectual level.
You will find me travelling, learning traditions, dancing and relaxing in the sun.
You will find me loving life, smiling, and laughing.
You will find me out and about, come to say hello, I am friendly, I want to know, where will I find you, what makes you grow?
United we will create a better world, where we belong, where we fit in :) #NewYearResolution #BetterMeCreateABetterWorld #IBelongWithYou #Quoted #HappyIslamicNewYear1437

Happy 50th Birthday to the second man I fall in love too!!! (The first one is my Indonesian father, since I met him earlier than you dad. So he is the first and you are the second and I am still waiting for the third, hihihi... Anyway...) I can't be more grateful to God for giving me such a wisest man to call as my dad. Thank you for teaching me all the life lesson, dad. I still remember this word you said to me when I was sad about something, "Febry, you are a nice person, but not everyone is nice. So if someone treating you bad, even if you always treat them nice, it's okay. Because, remember, there is always a bad person in this world, no matter what. So just continue to being nice". And by the end of the day, when I am feeling so exhausted about everything, I remember what you said. I am a nice person, and I am just going to behave and act like a nice person should be.
Dad, thank you for all the daddy-protectiveness you give to me. I really appreciate it. In truth, it made me feel more safety and secure, because I know I have a dad that going to protect me from all the bad person in this world.
Dad, you will always be my star. Sometimes, it might be hard to see your light because of the thickness of the cloud or just because of the distance between us. But I know, you are always there for me, just like the star that's always there in the sky.
Dad, 50 is a big number. I can't believe you already half of the century. It is going to be a golden year, dad. Remember what I said last night? Watch out! You might be turning to gold by the end of the day. Lol... hihihi... Anyway, I wish you a very happy birthday, daddy! You are always in my thought and prayer. 
I love you dad.

Your daughter,
-Febry Rambo-
